Rear-revisited 
I installed coil over shocks to raise the rear of my 71. I noticed a
definite improvement in the handling and stability at highway speeds,
which is, of course, my opinion. The improvement, real or percieved,
could be due to the increased overall spring rate rather than purely due
to raising the rear, or a combination of both - who knows? 
